The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for partitioning a graph into k pieces, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm involves processing nodes in a distributed manner, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.PF). The paper also discusses techniques for minimizing the total cut size, which is a problem in optimization (cs.LG) and network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to Google Maps Driving Directions, which involves network analysis and optimization, as well as networking and information retrieval (cs.NI).
